# signal-second-opinion

Cross-model second-opinion reviews. No external deps — pure stdlib.

## When to use
- Request a review: `signalos signal-second-opinion "Plan: X" --wave 15`
- Record verdict: `signalos signal-second-opinion-record so-001 --verdict disagree --new-risk "Y"`

## Key behaviours
- Reviews stored at `.signalos/second-opinion/index.jsonl` (append-only)
- Sequential IDs: `so-001`, `so-002`, ...
- Reviewer must use a fresh system prompt — no prior session context
- Disagree/risk-identified verdicts should be recorded in DECISION-DNA
